======================================================================
8) HIGH-VALUE META PROMPTS (COPY ANYTIME)
======================================================================

1. Topic simplifier prompt:
"Teach [TOPIC] in 3 layers: beginner intuition, exam-level detail, and interview-level depth. Include diagrams in text form and memory tricks."

2. PYQ style prompt:
"Generate 20 previous-year style descriptive questions on [TOPIC], then provide model answers and marking scheme."

3. Viva trainer prompt:
"Act as strict viva examiner for [TOPIC]. Ask one question at a time, wait for my answer, then give feedback and next question."

4. Notes maker prompt:
"Convert [TOPIC] into one-page revision notes with headings, formulas, pitfalls, and 10 rapid-fire questions."

5. Weakness fixer prompt:
"I am weak in [TOPIC]. Diagnose my weak points through 10 diagnostic questions and give a 7-day recovery plan."

6. Lab record prompt:
"For [LAB EXPERIMENT], generate complete record file format: aim, apparatus, theory, procedure, observation table, calculations, result, precautions, viva."

7. YouTube companion prompt:
"I watched a YouTube lecture on [TOPIC]. Ask me conceptual questions to check understanding, then give correction and better explanation where I fail."

8. Interview conversion prompt:
"Convert [TOPIC] from academic theory into interview discussion format with practical examples and common follow-up questions."


======================================================================
9) TWO-YEAR DIFFICULT EXECUTION STRATEGY (WITH CHATBOT)
======================================================================

Year 1:
1. Sem1+Sem2 foundation subjects complete with prompts.
2. Daily: 1 concept prompt + 1 practice prompt + 1 viva prompt.
3. Weekly: 1 mini project progression update.

Year 2:
1. Sem3-Sem6 deep core + selected specialization.
2. Weekly: 2 interview prep sessions using prompts.
3. Monthly: one project milestone with documentation.

Extra 6 months:
1. Capstone excellence.
2. Placement prep and mock interview cycles.
3. Portfolio polishing with strong project storytelling.


